															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/prattler" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1507358); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1507358&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204474" alt="Prattler" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1507358)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/prattler" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1507358); return false;" >Prattler</a></span> <span class="odate time_1355335385 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Dec 2012 18:03</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1648670">
									

<p>Firstly, thanks man for your comment, much appreciated.</p>
<p>Secondly, to answer some of your confusions, no, this is not a current SCP, it is a SCP I am currently working on, I came up with the idea when I was writing this short story for a project, I decided after finding this site a while ago to try and make it into a full-blown SCP. This short story as I explained in my first comment was &quot;gathering dust on my desktop&quot;, and I thought it might be a good way to introduce the SCP before it was released for all to see. Due to the SCP not existing as of now, I have changed the tags from &quot;tale&quot; to &quot;creepypasta&quot; as of your thoughts.</p>
<p>As with all tales or creepypasta on this site, I believe, they are up for interpretation and this is no exception. All people have their fears, thats a given, and mine is in the form of a crude ragdoll, I had as a child. Everyone elses on this site may differ, and thats awesome, it's what this site is built on, various fears potrayed in realistic manners.</p>
<p>Anyways, I went on a tangent, thanks for your thoughts they are much appreciated.</p>

							</div>

								
