			<div class="content" id="post-content-1648741">
									

<p>Not bad. I didn't like it enough to upvote, but I feel it was good enough to save it from a downvote. I feel like there was a bit too much build-up and not that much pay-off. WARNING: PERSONAL OPINIONS AND SUGGESTIONS AHEAD. The narrative of the childhood was a little bland; I would personally make it more <em>meaningful</em> and interesting by possibly changing the tone, maybe to, for example, emptily melancholy or happy naïvety. Also, it really feels like you just skimmed over what could possibly be the most interesting part of the story when you just briefly hint at the acquisition of the teeth.</p>
<p>To recap: Not bad, but could be better. No vote.</p>
<p>As a sidenote, the description reminded me of the Lilo and Stitch doll.</p>

